The paper discusses multi-task learning in computer vision applications, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a framework for assigning tasks to neural networks, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses task cooperation and competition, which suggests that it may belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category, as it discusses the use of neural networks for solving multiple tasks simultaneously.
